Should report a warning for the implicit call to `s.Value.GetEnumerator()`:
```C#
using System.Collections;

struct S : IEnumerable
{
    public IEnumerator GetEnumerator() => throw null;
}

class Program
{
    static void F(S? s)
    {
        foreach (var i in s)
        {
        }
    }

    static void Main()
    {
        F(null);
    }
}
```

Warnings should be reported for `x.Value` and `y.Value`:
```C#
class Program
{
    static void F<T>(T t) where T : struct
    {
        T? x = new System.Nullable<T>();
        _ = x.Value; // should warn
        T? y = new T?();
        _ = y.Value; // should warn
    }
}
```

```C#
class Program
{
    static T F<T>(T? x) where T : struct
    {
        return (T)x!;
    }
}
```
Expected Result: No warnings

Actual Result:
```
(5,19): warning CS8624: The suppression operator (!) can only be applied to reference types.
(5,16): warning CS8629: Nullable value type may be null.
```

No warning should be reported for `y.Value`:
```C#
class Program
{
    static void F1(int? x)
    {
        if (x == null) return;
        var y = ~x;
        _ = y.Value; // warning: nullable value type may be null
    }
}
```

